The paper deals with a wireless relay network and its capacity approximation. The use of compress-and-forward strategy and quantization of signals are discussed, which are common topics in information theory (cs.IT) and networking (cs.NI). The paper also mentions time-varying networks, which falls under the category of signal processing (cs.SI). The use of Gaussian codebooks and capacity gaps are related to machine learning (cs.MM) and learning theory (cs.LG).
